  "articleBody": "<!-- Page 7 --><article>\n\n\n\n            <h6 class=\"yellow\">Scene of the asceticism of John in the distance of the central panel</h6>\n\n              <p>He then leads an exemplary life as an ascetic «in the desert» <span style=\"color: #999;\">(Luke chapter 1 verse 80)</span>.</p>\n              <p>Memling transposes this scene into the forest.</p>\n\n            <figure>\n              <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-280.webp 280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-380.webp 380w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-480.webp 480w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-640.webp 640w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-840.webp 840w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-1280.webp 1280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-1600.webp 1600w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “John the Baptist praying in the forest”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “John the Baptist praying in the forest”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-40-img\" width=\"517\" height=\"794\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-280.jpg 280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-380.jpg 380w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-480.jpg 480w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-640.jpg 640w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-840.jpg 840w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-1280.jpg 1280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-1600.jpg 1600w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/priere-dans-le-desert-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the central panel, “John the Baptist praying in the forest”</figcaption>\n            </figure>\n\n\n\n            <h6 class=\"yellow\">Scene of the apostolate of John in the distance of the central panel</h6>\n\n              <p>We also see him <q cite=\"https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Bible_(World_English)/Luke#3:3\" style=\"quotes: '«' '»';\">preaching the baptism of repentance for remission of sins</q> <span style=\"color: #999;\">(Luke chapter 3 verse 3)</span>.</p>\n\n            <figure>\n              <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-280.webp 280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-380.webp 380w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-480.webp 480w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-640.webp 640w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-840.webp 840w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-1280.webp 1280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-1600.webp 1600w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/proclamation-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “John the Baptist proclaiming a baptism of conversion for the forgiveness of sins”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “John the Baptist proclaiming a baptism of conversion for the forgiveness of sins”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-40-img\" width=\"548\" height=\"738\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-280.jpg 280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-380.jpg 380w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-480.jpg 480w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-640.jpg 640w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-840.jpg 840w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-1280.jpg 1280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-1600.jpg 1600w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/proclamation-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the central panel, “John the Baptist <q cite=\"https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Bible_(World_English)/Luke#3:3\" style=\"quotes: '' '';\">preaching the baptism of repentance for remission of sins</q>”</figcaption>\n            </figure>\n\n              <p>John innovates in the judaism of his time.</p>\n              <p>He advocates the forgiveness of sins no longer through the sacrifice of animals in the temple by cremation, but by <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">«baptism»</span>, that is, according to the etymology of the word, <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">«immersion»</span> in water.</p>\n\n\n\n\n            <h6 class=\"yellow\">Scene of John the Baptist baptizing Jesus on the banks of the Jordan River in the far left inner shutter</h6>\n            \n              <p>According to the biblical writings, he <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">announces the coming of god's envoy</span> in the person of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Historical_Jesus\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Historical_Jesus\" class=\"yellow\">Jesus of Nazareth</a>, one of his contemporaries.</p>\n              <p>He recognizes it by a baptism in the waters of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jordan_River\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jordan_River\" id=\"jourdain\" class=\"yellow\">Jordan</a>: this scene appears at the top of the left inner shutter.</p>\n\n            <figure>\n              <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-280.webp 280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-380.webp 380w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-480.webp 480w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-640.webp 640w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-840.webp 840w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-1280.webp 1280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-1600.webp 1600w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/baptème-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the inner left panel, “John the Baptist baptizing Jesus on the banks of the Jordan River”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the inner left panel, “John the Baptist baptizing Jesus on the banks of the Jordan River”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-40-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"547\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-280.jpg 280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-380.jpg 380w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-480.jpg 480w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-640.jpg 640w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-840.jpg 840w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-1280.jpg 1280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-1600.jpg 1600w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/baptème-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the inner left panel, “John the Baptist baptizing Jesus on the banks of the Jordan River”</figcaption>\n            </figure>\n\n              <p>On the other bank, <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">John the Baptist</span> presents Jesus with the words <q cite=\"https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Bible_(World_English)/John#1:35\" style=\"color: #e6a64d;quotes: '«' '»'\"><ruby style=\"color:#e6a64d;\" lang=\"en\">Behold the lamb of god<rp>(</rp><rt style=\"color:#e6a64d;font-size: 70%;letter-spacing: 2px;\" lang=\"la\">Ecce agnus dei</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby></q> to his first two disciples <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_the_Apostle\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_the_Apostle\" id=\"andre\" class=\"yellow\">Andrew</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_the_Apostle\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_the_Apostle\" id=\"jean-l-apotre\" class=\"yellow\">John the Apostle</a>; they join him.</p>\n\n\n\n\n            <h6 class=\"yellow\">Scene of the arrest of John in the distance of the central panel</h6>\n\n              <p>From that point on, his story turns to tragedy.</p>\n              <p>The tetrarch of Galilee and Perea, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herod_Antipas\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herod_Antipas\" id=\"herode-antipas\" class=\"yellow\">Herod Antipas</a> married «<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herod_II\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herod_II\" id=\"herode-boethos\" class=\"yellow\">his brother Philip's wife</a> (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herodias\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herodias\" id=\"herodiade\">Herodias</a>)» <span style=\"color: #999;\">(Mark chapter 6, verse 17)</span>;</p>\n              <p>As the jewish faith regards any marriage with his brother's wife as <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">«defiling»</span> and <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">forbids</span> it <span style=\"color: #999;\">(Leviticus chapter 18 verse 16; chapter 20 verse 21)</span>, John publicly condemns it.</p>\n              <p><span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">Herod feared</span> that this would provoke «<span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">a revolt</span>, the crowd seeming ready to follow all the advice of this man.</p>\n              <p>He therefore prefers to take him before any trouble occurs because of him, rather than to have to repent later if a movement takes place» <span style=\"color: #999;\">(<cite>Jewish Antiquities</cite>, Book XVIII, chapter 5, paragraph 118)</span>.</p>\n              <p>In the event of unrest caused by John's supporters, Herod had to answer to the roman authorities, who could dismiss him:</p>\n              <p>he gives <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">“the order to arrest John”</span> <span style=\"color: #999;\">(Mark chapter 6, verse 17)</span>.</p>\n\n            <figure>\n              <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-280.webp 280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-380.webp 380w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-480.webp 480w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-640.webp 640w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-840.webp 840w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-1280.webp 1280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-1600.webp 1600w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/arrestation-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “Arrest of John the Baptist by order of Herod Antipas”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “Arrest of John the Baptist by order of Herod Antipas”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-diane-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"1154\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-280.jpg 280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-380.jpg 380w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-480.jpg 480w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-640.jpg 640w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-840.jpg 840w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-1280.jpg 1280w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-1600.jpg 1600w,\n              /docs/saint-jean/arrestation-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the central panel, “Arrest of John the Baptist by order of Herod Antipas”</figcaption>\n            </figure>\n\n              <p>On the central panel above the white lamb, <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">John was forcibly taken</span> to the prison on the left side of the current city of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machaerus\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machaerus\" id=\"macheronte\" class=\"yellow\"><ruby style=\"color:#e6a64d;\" lang=\"en\">Machaerus<rp>(</rp><rt style=\"color:#e6a64d;font-size: 70%;letter-spacing: 2px;\" lang=\"la\">μάχαιρα</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby></a>, whose ethymology in ancient greek means «sword» and which is located in present-day Jordan.</p>\n\n\n\n</article>"
